\title{Miasm Symbolic}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{description}{Miasm reverse engineering framework for symbolic execution, IR lifting, and binary analysis. Interoperates with blackhat-go via adversarial bisimulation games and GF(3) conservation.}

\subtree{
\title{Miasm Symbolic Execution Skill}
\p{\strong{Status}: ✅ Production Ready \strong{Source}: CEA-SEC Miasm Framework (3.8K stars) \strong{Interop}: blackhat-go adversarial bisimulation games \strong{GF(3)}: ERGODIC (0) - transformation/mediation role}

\subtree{
\title{Conscious Hacker Integration Philosophy}
\p{The conscious hacker recognizes that \strong{offensive and defensive security are dual}:}

\pre{\startverb
blackhat-go (attack chains) ←→ miasm-symbolic (program understanding)
        ↓                              ↓
   Order matters (Ungar)        State equivalence (Bisim)
        ↓                              ↓
    MINUS (-1)                    ERGODIC (0)
\stopverb}

\p{Together with a \strong{defense verification} skill (+1), this maintains GF(3) conservation.}
}

\subtree{
\title{Overview}
\p{Miasm provides:}

\ul{
\li{\strong{16 Architectures}: x86_16/32/64, ARM, MIPS, AArch64, PPC, SH4, MSP430, MEP}
\li{\strong{IR Lifting}: Assembly → Intermediate Representation}
\li{\strong{Symbolic Execution}: Constraint solving for path exploration}
\li{\strong{Emulation}: JIT-based binary emulation}
\li{\strong{DSE}: Dynamic Symbolic Execution}
}
}

